snippet: Prime Minister David Cameron on Tuesday canceled a trip to Israel and the Palestinian territories to deal with extraordinary flooding in England.
abstract: British Prime Min David Cameron cancels trip to Israel and Palestinian territory in order to deal with extraordinary flooding in England; trip would have been his first visit to region as prime minister.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister David Cameron on Tuesday canceled a trip to Israel and the Palestinian territories to deal with extraordinary flooding in England.

headline.main: Britain: Thames Flooding Causes Cameron to Skip Middle East Visit
headline.print_headline: Britain: Thames Flooding Causes Cameron to Skip Middle East Visit
